calcMaxCardMapping

public void calcMaxCardMapping(java.lang.Boolean[][] G1,
                               java.lang.Boolean[][] G2,
                               double[][] mappingScores,
                               double threshHold)
Calculates p-Hom Mapping from Nodes of G1 to G2. i.e. The Direction of p-Homomorphism is G1 p-HOM G2 When Matching Web Service Input-Outputs : G1 -> IODAG for Input (ofCandidateOp) and G2 -> IODAG for Output (ofWorkflowOp)

Parameters:
G1 - Adjacency Matrix Representation of Graph1
G2 - Adjacency Matrix Representation of Graph2
mappingScores - Matrix that stores Match scores for every node v in G1 to every node v' in graph V2
threshHold - value between 0-1 s.t. v-v' matches scoring above it will only be considered
